description:
The existing ScoreBreakdown model uses a flat justifications: dict[str, str] field — one plain string per category. The new feature replaces this with a structured per-category breakdown object carrying five fields: reasoning, gap_analysis, improvements (list), short_learning_path (list), and long_learning_path (list).

This is a non-breaking addition to the response contract (the four integer score fields and job_fit_adjusted remain unchanged) but it replaces the justifications field entirely, so it is effectively a breaking change to that field's shape.

Work required:
1. Update architecture/api-interfaces.md:
   - Section 6 (Pydantic Models): replace the ScoreBreakdown model definition with the new one. Introduce a new CategoryBreakdown sub-model and update ScoreBreakdown.justifications type from dict[str, str] to dict[str, CategoryBreakdown].
   - Section 7 (TypeScript Types): mirror the same change in the TypeScript interface block. Add a CategoryBreakdown interface and update ScoreBreakdown.justifications accordingly.
   - Section 4 (Endpoints): update the COMPLETED example response to show one category with the new nested structure (the other three can be shown abbreviated).

2. Update architecture/architecture.md if it references the ScoreBreakdown justifications shape anywhere (check the scoring section).

New Pydantic sub-model to document:

```python
class CategoryBreakdown(BaseModel):
    reasoning: str          # HOW the score was calculated (formula + inputs)
    gap_analysis: str       # What is missing to reach max points
    improvements: list[str] # Specific actionable items (1-3 bullet strings)
    short_learning_path: list[str]  # Quick wins, weeks to 1-2 months (1-2 items)
    long_learning_path: list[str]   # Strategic improvements, 3-6 months (1-2 items)
```

Updated ScoreBreakdown:
```python
class ScoreBreakdown(BaseModel):
    experience:      int
    skills:          int
    education:       int
    role_seniority:  int
    total:           int
    justifications:  dict[str, CategoryBreakdown]  # was dict[str, str]
    job_fit_adjusted: bool
```

Mirror TypeScript interface:
```typescript
export interface CategoryBreakdown {
  reasoning: string;
  gap_analysis: string;
  improvements: string[];
  short_learning_path: string[];
  long_learning_path: string[];
}

export interface ScoreBreakdown {
  experience: number;
  skills: number;
  education: number;
  role_seniority: number;
  total: number;
  justifications: Record<'experience' | 'skills' | 'education' | 'role_seniority', CategoryBreakdown>;
  job_fit_adjusted: boolean;
}
```

Acceptance criteria:
- architecture/api-interfaces.md reflects the CategoryBreakdown sub-model in both Pydantic and TypeScript sections.
- The COMPLETED response example in section 4 shows at least one category with all five new fields populated.
- architecture/architecture.md is updated if the scoring section referenced the old justifications shape.
- No implementation code is written in this task.
